{
  "stem": "10572.6",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You know, it's actually January 15th.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "January 15th,--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--1996.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When-- when we finally left Germany on that 23rd of June, 1939, and my parents and my younger sister took us to the train, and it was this bloodletting experience that we had experienced so often of saying farewell without knowing if you would ever see them again, if they would ever see us again.",
      "word_count": 55
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I still see the-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] --the white handkerchiefs, you know, disappearing.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And-- but we somehow felt that we were getting closer to the possibility of getting my parents and my younger sister out.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we went to-- we went to a-- to a-- to the border, Aachen.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Aachen was the border before we got into Belgium on our way to England.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And in Aachen, we were taken off the train-- all of the people that were going to the Lord Kitchener Camp-- for final examination.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And after they-- after the Nazis had stolen, robbed, thieved everything we ever owned, here we were going through an examination, where we-- the most unbelievable examination I've ever gone through, where we had to undress and we had to bend over.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They wanted to see if we had hidden diamonds.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And we were checked out.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I felt later on that they had saved no effort to make our leaving Germany as easy as possible for us.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And we couldn't wait.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And then we went through Belgium, and we arrived in England.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We saw the White Cliffs of Dover in contrast to all the darkness and blackness that we left behind.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And we met these wonderful people, and I have always been fond and grateful for the unbelievable hospitality that the English offered us.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And in the Lord Kitchener Camp-- the camp was self sufficient.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
